bugs.suggestedFix:
Add `display: none` to the `.header` rule inside the ≤700px media query in App.module.css. This completely removes it from layout on mobile.

```css
/* Inside @media (max-width: 700px) */
.header {
  display: none;
}
```

Also remove or guard the ≤480px `.header` padding override (line 273) since it's no longer needed when the header is hidden on mobile.

Note: The safe-area-inset-top padding previously on `.header` should be moved to `.app` if not already there, to preserve status bar spacing on PWA/notched devices.
